# Ignition Tag System
---

1. Where to Find Tags

    ![Find Tags](/images/tags/tags0.jpg)
    - You can find the tags folder in the bottom left corner of the Ignition Designer.

2. User Defined Tag (UDT) Definitions
    
    ![UDT Definitions](/images/tags/tags1.jpg)
    - First make sure you're in the proper directory by clicking the dropdown of the Tag Browser and navigating to "default."
    - Then click on the UDT Definitions to see the User Defined Tag Defintions.
    - Right-click on the "home" tag and click "Edit tag(s)" to see more info.

3. Home Tag
    
    ![Home Tag](/images/tags/tags2.jpg)
    - This is the home tag details. You can see the type structure has it being the parent of six child tags.
    
    ![control1 tag](/images/tags/tags3.jpg)
    - To better understand how the tag is used, click on the scripting tab below for the control1 tag.
    - The control1 tag controls the Yellow LED.
    
4. Tag Scripting

    ![Tag Scripting](/images/tags/tags4.jpg)
    - def valueChanged(tag, tagPath, previousValue, currentValue, initialChange, missedEvents):
        - This runs whenever the tag value changes.
	
    - if initialChange:
	-   return
        - If the tag value is the same as its previous value, the function returns.
    - path = system.tag.readBlocking("[~]NamespaceHome/Concat")[0].value
    - fullpath = path + '/control1'
        - It gets the path for publishing to the MQTT broker module. 
	- system.cirruslink.engine.publish('MQTT_Broker', fullpath, currentValue.value, 0, 0)
        - Publishes to the MQTT Broker using the namespace path.

